# Admin System Architectural Audit & Fix Plan

## Goal Description
Conduct a rigorous, real-world business audit of the "RepairMyBike" Admin ecosystem, focusing on the true CRUD capabilities for Services, Spare Parts, and Subscriptions. The objective is to identify the "Truth Gap" between the frontend UI presentation and the actual backend data capabilities, ensuring the system is truly production-ready.

---

## STEP 1: UNDERSTAND ADMIN WORKFLOW (REAL WORLD)

If I am a business admin managing a mechanic shop platform, I require absolute control over my catalog. 

1. **Services**: I need to define the Name, Category, Rich Description, SEO tags, Pricing Tiers (by bike model), **Active/Inactive Status** (to hide seasonal services), Included Parts (Specs), and a **Gallery of Images** showing the service being performed.
2. **Spare Parts**: I need to manage Inventory Qty, Name, Brand, Category, SKU, MRP, Sale Price, **Dimensions/Weight** (for shipping), **Warranty Details** (Months, Pro-Rata), Technical Specs, an **Active/Inactive Status**, and a **Multi-Image Gallery**.
3. **Subscriptions**: I need to define the Plan Name, Banner/Hero Image, Tier (Basic/Premium), Duration (Billing Period), Price, Discount Price, a structured list of **Benefits**, a list of **Included Services**, and an **Active/Inactive Status**.

---

## STEP 2: MODEL vs REAL REQUIREMENT GAP

| Domain | Model Analysis | Verdict |
|--------|---------------|---------|
| **Services** | ❌ Missing `active` (status) field. Admin cannot hide a service without deleting it! ⚠️ Has `images` as a single `ImageField`, but a service realistically requires a gallery (multiple images). | 🟡 **Weak** |
| **Spare Parts** | ✅ Excellent model. Contains `sku`, `mrp`, `sale_price`, `stock_qty`, `warranty_months_total`, `active` flag, and a dedicated `SparePartImage` model for a robust image gallery. | 🟢 **Good** |
| **Subscriptions** | ✅ Good fields. Has `price`, `discount_price`, `billing_period`, `active`, and `included_services` (M2M). ⚠️ Contains legacy JSON fields (`benefits` and `services`) alongside structured tables (`PlanBenefit`), which causes data duplication. | 🟢 **Good** |

